Geo Map Reference

ThoughtSpot recognizes and supports a broad list of geographic regions and their subdivisions.

This reference lists supported countries and their subdivisions. ThoughtSpot renders these regions in geo maps.

Download the supported geo maps CSV file

You can download a CSV file that contains all supported values for geo map countries, codes, and subdivisions. Use this file to confirm that your own geographical values are in the correct format, and that ThoughtSpot supports them. Download the CSV file.

The CSV file contains leading 0s when these zeros are present for ThoughtSpot at the beginning of zip/post code values. However, if you import this file into Excel or another spreadsheet tool, that tool may remove leading zeros, resulting in data that does not match ThoughtSpot’s format.

Supported countries and subdivisions

ThoughtSpot supports the following countries and their associated subdivisions:
